task.summary: Default task
StackTrace, etc. are all working, except Addr2Line hasn't been implemented yet.
Fixed String_format().
Started work on Addr2Line.

Added a maxDepth argument to StackTrace, so that only part of the stack can be examined if wanted. Also typedef'd number of stack frames to stack_size_t.
Making (slow) progress on Addr2Line.

Added StackTrace_walk() and StackTrace_walkArg() that traverse the StackTrace with a StackWalker callback.
installed libs: libbfd-dev libiberty-dev

StackTrace works flawlessly w/o optimizations. Must test with optimizations, which will cause inlining (also untested, probably doesn't work). When the stack size is very high (>1000), bfd_openr() starts throwing file not found
Included elf-bfd.h from source (downloaded from RedoxOS/binutils-gdb from GitHub).
Forgot to zero out programNameChars[] in getProgramName(), which was causing the string not to be null-terminated when the stack size was very large.

Have to completely fix inline function handling in Addr2Line. Works up to -02, but breaks at -03. Doesn't even recognize correct function (StackTrace_init() mistaken for StackTrace_print()), which shouldn't be part of the call stack.
Also merged Addr2Line_findOffsetInSection() with Addr2Line_findAddressInSection().
Fixed memory leaks w/ Valgrind for StackTraceSignalHandler.

The bug where StackTrace_print() is included in the StackTrace even though it shouldn't be in the call stack doesn't seem to be related to my code. Using addr2line on the command line, it shows StackTrace_print() too. Using the address printed out automatically from backtrace after the program dies with addr2line shows StackTrace_print() too. When I add the -fno-inline-small-functions flag, it works fine.

When I add __attribute__ ((noinline)) to StackTrace_print(), it no longer shows up in the StackTrace or addr2line backtrace; StackTrace_printNow() shows up instead, which is correct.
When I run addr2line with -i to show inlined functions, it says StackTrace_print() is inlined by StackTrace_printNow(). This is probably true, but the call stack still shouldn't include StackTrace_print(). I guess this is just the way backtrace() and ELF work.
I need to rework how StackTrace processes inlining (not inlined, but the inliner) functions. The linked list method I've been trying still seems like a good option, but I'll need to interpret it differently. If the inlined function is never actually part of the call stack, like StackTrace_print(), I'll probably just ignore it, but it StackTrace_print() is just a special case, I'll have to figure something else out. I'll also probably write a way to flatten the StackTrace.

Fixed handling inlined functions.
Weirdly inlined functions that aren't actually part of the call stack, like StackTrace_print(), still show up, but that's a problem with backtrace().
Changed bool StackFrame.isInlined to stack_size_t StackFrame.inlinedDepth. This is calculated recursively and then allows StackTrace to keep track of the total number of frames, including inlined frames, in stack_size_t StackTrace.totalNumFrames.
StackTrace_toString() now uses StackTrace_walkArg() so that the array loop and linked list loop aren't repeated.
Just need to resolve the correct executable file (shared library) from StackFrame.message when it is a dynamically linked function, like from libc.so, meaning Addr2Line doesn't work normally since the executable file is wrong.
Fixed a bug in String_copy() and String_concat(). Refactored into String_appendBytesUnchecked().

Added hashing to String.
Will now try to create a generic collections library using macros. Need HashMap<String, Addr2Line> for good performance.

Started creating generated, type-safe, generic HashMap in MakeMake (TS).
Although the HashMap isn't finished yet, I integrated it's headers into Addr2Line to cache other Addr2Line's for shared libraries.
In Addr2Line, I only have to finish implementing SharedLibraryAddress_parseFromMessage().
Implemented SharedLibraryAddress_parseFromMessage().
Reorganized directory structure. Modularized CMakeLists.txt and added static library target with lto. For lto, need to manually fix CMakeCache.txt: ar=gcc-ar ranlib=gcc-ranlib
Wrote a Makefile that finds and compiles all files with correct dependencies. Outputs everything in bin/, including .d dependency sub Makefiles.
Added .PHONY's to Makefile.
Fixed memory leaks.
Removed old Makefile.
Fixing git author name.
